I"b<h1 id="virtual-misls">Virtual MISLS</h1>

<!-- ![virtual-misls](/assets/img/virtual-misls/hall-fullwidth.png) -->

<p>Virtual MISLS is a virtual tour of the Military Intelligence Service Language School at Fort Snelling, Minnesota.</p>

<p>During World War II, the MISLS trained soldiers in the Japanese language to aid the war effort. Since then, many of buildings have fallen into disrepair. We created this virtual tour to enable people to immerse themselves in a part of history that is often under-represented at Fort Snelling.</p>

<ul class="subtitle">
<li>Faculty project lead: <a href="https://cla.umn.edu/about/directory/profile/kathayes" target="_blank">Dr. Katherine Hayes</a></li>
<li>Programmer: <a href="https://danielshervheim.com/" target="_blank">Dan Shervheim</a></li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

